  "texts": [
    "It is evident that the 'lensing residuals' derived from the two methods are quite similar (with a difference of O(1)%), which represents the residual lensing signal power.",
    "However, although they exhibit similar performance, their mechanisms are different.",
    "The Gradient-order template method is defined to subtract the gradient-order lensing effect at the map level, with parts of the highorder terms eliminated when using the lensed QU fields as input, it encounters high-order cancellations when calculating the power spectrum on large scales.",
    "In contrast, the Inverselensing method inherently aims to eliminate the lensing effect by definition.",
    "Therefore, we believe the Inverse-lensing method is the optimal one with more accuracy on all scales by definition."
  ],
